
     NAME
          icwinfo - write a information record  on a 'ic'-formatted 
                    file 

     FORTRAN F77 SPECIFICATION
          integer function icwinfo(iu,ra,ras,iddc,rle,numx,numy)
          integer*4 iu, iddc, numx, numy
          real*4    ra, ras, rle

     PARAMETERS

         INPUT:
         iu     = file unit, can range from 1 to 25
         ra     = thermal Rayleigh number
         ras    = chemical Rayleigh number
         niter  = numer of model iteration
         iddc   = double-diffusive convection 0 = .false., 1 = .true.
         rle    = the lewis number
         numx   = number of point in x-direction
         numy   = number of point in y-direction

     RETURNS
         0      =  fine

     DESCRIPTION
         icwinfo writes an information record on the data-file.

     KNOWN PROBLEMS
         iddc is an integer and not a logical variable

     SEE ALSO
         icopen, icwinfo, icwrite, icskip, icrinfo, icread, icback, 
         icclose,ictools

